  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best resources to learn AngularJs2 and Typescript?",
  "response": "Learning Angular and TypeScript involves a combination of official documentation, online courses, tutorials, books, and community resources. Here are some of the best resources to get started and deepen your understanding:\n\n### Official Documentation\n1. **Angular's Official Website**: \n   - The Angular documentation is extensive and well-organized, making it a great starting point for learning Angular concepts, features, and best practices.\n   - [Angular Documentation](https://angular.io/docs)\n\n2. **TypeScript Official Website**:\n   - Provides comprehensive documentation about TypeScript, including a beginner's guide and detailed language specifications.\n   - [TypeScript Documentation](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/)\n\n### Online Courses\n1. **Udemy**:\n   - Courses like \"The Complete Guide (2023 Edition)\" by Maximilian Schwarzm\u00fcller offer detailed, hands-on learning experiences.\n   - \"Angular - The Complete Guide\" is particularly popular for beginners to intermediate learners.\n\n2. **Coursera**:\n   - Offers a range of courses focusing on Angular and TypeScript, often in collaboration with universities or top tech companies.\n\n3. **Pluralsight**:\n   - Provides many courses on Angular and TypeScript, from beginner to advanced levels, including best practices and real-world applications.\n\n4. **Frontend Masters**:\n   - Has courses such as \"Angular Fundamentals\" and \"Intermediate TypeScript,\" which go in-depth into the topics.\n\n### Books\n1. **\"Angular Development with TypeScript\" by Yakov Fain and Anton Moiseev**:\n   - A comprehensive guide covering how to develop applications using Angular in conjunction with TypeScript.\n\n2. **\"Pro Angular\" by Adam Freeman**:\n   - An in-depth resource for understanding Angular and applying it to real-world projects.\n\n3. **\"Learning TypeScript\" by Borislav Hadzhiev**:\n   - A detailed guide for beginners to get started with TypeScript and how to integrate it within Angular.\n\n### Tutorials and Blogs\n1. **Angular University**:\n   - Offers a variety of free and paid tutorials for learning Angular concepts.\n\n2. **Scotch.io and Medium**:\n   - Contains numerous articles and tutorials on both Angular and TypeScript.\n\n3. **Dev.to Community**:\n   - Has many posts, tutorials, and shared experiences by developers who are using Angular and TypeScript.\n\n### Other Resources\n1. **YouTube**:\n   - Channels such as Academind, Traversy Media, and Net Ninja provide free tutorials and practical Angular project examples.\n\n2. **GitHub**:\n   - Explore popular repositories to see examples of Angular projects, and contribute to open-source projects to get hands-on experience.\n\n3. **Stack Overflow**:\n   - An invaluable resource for troubleshooting and learning through community Q&A.\n\nWhen starting, it's often beneficial to work on small projects or contribute to open-source libraries to apply what you've learned practically. Additionally, joining Angular and TypeScript communities, whether online or locally, can provide support and deepen your understanding through networking.",
